<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 04 at 4:54PM CDT until August 04 at 5:30PM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 530 PM CDT
FOR PIKE AND SOUTHEASTERN MONTGOMERY COUNTIES...
At 454 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Troy Municipal
Airport, or 7 miles north of Troy, moving southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Troy, Goshen, Meadville, Banks, Pine Level, Kent, Strata, Dublin,
Naftel, Linwood, Ansley, Grady, Sellers, Troy Municipal Airport,
Ramer, Troy University, Lapine, Monticello, Orion and Josie.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
